The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Ian Gould in hospital
                                                                                                                       7                                      Ian Gould in hospital
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Umpire Ian Gould was admitted to a private hospital in the city with gastroenteritis soon after the Eden Test.         
	Gould was admitted with acute dehydration at around 6:45 pm. He was diagnosed with gastroenteritis. He has been administered intravenous fluid and antibiotics, said an official of Woodlands Hospital, Calcutta.         
	He will be kept under observation till tomorrow (Friday) morning, after which the doctors will assess his situation. His flight is at 2 in the afternoon on Friday, but if doctors think so, he may have to stay back, CAB joint secretary Biswarup Dey said.                                                                                                                     
